cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CE, cs.SOC, cs.LG

This paper involves the study of forecasting models using large scale microblog discussions and search behavior data, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of causative relationships and unified approaches to model various market securities, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also investigates the lagged and statistically causative relations of Twitter sentiments developed during active trading days and market inactive days, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical models for forecasting, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
